author: J-W Staff Reports
title: Game balls and gassers: KU at Oklahoma State
text:
Advertisement Game Balls 
Linebacker Joe Dineen made his second quarter, blind-side sack of quarterback Mason Rudolph hurt. A week after Dineen posted 10 tackles vs. Texas Tech, he went one better with 11 tackles, including a punishing sack. 
Wide receiver Tre’ Parmalee ran crisp routes, showed terrific hands, creatively ate up yards after the catch and generally was the team’s best player in catching six passes for 115 yards. Gassers 
Safety Bazie Bates IV had the roughest four-play sequence of any Jayhawk this season. I: Missed tackle; II: Missed tackle on receiver who had no trouble getting open on him; III: Pass interference; IV: Missed tackle. 
Oft-penalized right tackle Larry Mazyck was flagged for a pair of chop blocks and a clip. 
— See what people were saying about the game during KUsports.com's live blog . More news and notes from Kansas at Oklahoma State
